ablished since the 13th century and Gaelicized as <b>de Sutún</b>.","Jewish (from the former Ottoman Empire, including Syria): unexplained.","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>(bi) suthentune</i> ‘(at the place to the) south of the village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Setton","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avi, Ronit, Yossef.  French Andree, Henri, Jacques, Maryse.","Jewish (from the Ottoman Empire): altered form of   Sutton  .","English (Middlesex): variant of   Seaton  ."]}]},{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":54,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda Sutton was born on 23 December 1400, in Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England. She married Roger Jodrell II in 1420, in Derby, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 30 September 1487, in her hometown, at the age of 86."},"et":{"23 December 1400–30 September 1487":"23. detsember 1400–30. september 1487","1400–1463":"1400–1463","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1425–Male":"1425–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1400–1487":"1400–1487","25 December 1400":"25. detsember 1400","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","23 December 1400":"23. detsember 1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","30 September 1487":"30. september 1487","Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Derby, , Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"23 December 1400–30 September 1487":"23. joulukuuta 1400–30. syyskuuta 1487","1400–1463":"1400–1463","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1425–Male":"1425–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1400–1487":"1400–1487","25 December 1400":"25. joulukuuta 1400","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","23 December 1400":"23. joulukuuta 1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","30 September 1487":"30. syyskuuta 1487","Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England":"Burton upon Trent, Staffordshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Derby, , Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"23 December 1400–30 September 1487":"23 décembre 1400–30 septembre 1487","1400–1463":"1400–1463","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1425–Male":"1425–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1400–1487":"1400–1487","25 December 1400":"25 décembre 1400","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","23 December 1400":"23 décembre 1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1450":"1450","30 September 1487":"30 se